title: Bug 121170 - getColumnLabel() returns null before extraction and recognizable strings after extraction
OB: The method IMetaData.getColumnLabel() returns null values for column labels before data extraction, but returns recognizable strings for column labels after data extraction.
EB: The expected behavior is for the method IMetaData.getColumnLabel() to always return recognizable strings for column labels, regardless of whether data extraction has been performed or not.
SR: To reproduce the issue, call the method IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before and after data extraction, and observe the difference in the returned values.
